    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers to the Hailhzaqvla, or Heiltsuk language-speaking people that inhabit the area around Bella Bella, British Columbia. Historically, the people that inhabit Bella Bella have been referred to as "Bella Bella Indians." The correct term to refer to the larger culture, and to describe the art and artifacts of this people, is "Heiltsuk."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000047715/Black, Bella Bella (1997)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000047714/Heiltsuk Nation (2006)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Verwijst naar het volk in het gebied rond Bella Bella in Brits-Columbia dat de taal Hailhzaqvla, of Heiltsuk, spreekt. In het verleden werd het volk dat in Bella Bella leefde de 'Bella Bella-indianen' genoemd. De juiste term om naar de cultuur in brede zin te verwijzen en om de kunst en artefacten van dit volk te beschrijven is 'Heiltsuk'.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052384/Billard, De indianen (1978)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>指居住在英屬哥倫比亞省貝拉貝拉村附近，使用海爾薩克法拉語（Hailhzaqvla）或海爾楚克語的族群。歷史上，居住在貝拉貝拉地區的人被稱為「貝拉貝拉印第安人」。但以「海爾楚克（Heiltsuk）」一詞來描述這個族群的藝術和手工藝品，以及更廣義的文化是較為正確的用法。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
